      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk about a neurologist, i feel fine physically. it's more like an intuitive/sensory thing. and look, i've been tracking it. every time i get this specific static feeling in my teeth, a major liquidity sweep happens within minutes. it's too consistent to be a coincidence. if mainstream science hasn't caught up to how human biology can interface with high-frequency signals yet, fine, but doesn't it make sense that ultra-fast algorithmic oscillations could create some kind of field that a sensitive nervous system could detect? like, if you look at how some animals sense electromagnetic fields, why couldn't this be a version of that applied to data streams?",
